wb-zigbee2mqtt (1.2.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Add device discovery: parse bridge/devices exposes, create WB devices
  * Add real-time device state updates via zigbee2mqtt/{device} subscription
  * Add expose type mapping: numeric (10 types), binary, enum, text, composite
  * Add type constants: ExposeType, ExposeProperty, WbControlType
  * Add binary value conversion using value_on/value_off from exposes
  * Add device removal: clean up WB retain topics and unsubscribe on remove/leave
  * Skip device registration until interview completes (exposes available)
  * Skip devices with no mappable exposes
  * Add ControlMeta.format_value() for z2m-to-WB value conversion
  * Add RegisteredDevice cache to avoid recomputing controls on every message
  * Use ieee_address for WB device_id (unique, stable across renames)
  * Handle last_seen in epoch and ISO string formats
  * Handle SIGHUP for graceful shutdown on terminal close

 -- Victor Fedorov <victor.fedorov@wirenboard.com>  Mon, 17 Mar 2026 13:40:00 +0300

wb-zigbee2mqtt (1.1.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * Add bridge device with 10 controls: state, version, log level, log,
    permit join, device count, last joined, last left, last removed,
    update devices
  * Add en/ru translations for all bridge controls
  * Add bridge log filtering by level (bridge_log_min_level config)
  * Add device event tracking (joined, left, removed)
  * Extract WbZigbee2Mqtt class into app.py

